19/05/2009
PARIS, France -- President Nicolas Sarkozy on Monday (May 18th) met with visiting Romanian counterpart Traian Basescu and offered help in building a new nuclear power station. 
Sarkozy said Paris is ready to share its nuclear expertise and to encourage French companies to invest in the Romanian project to build a second plant. 
The two presidents also discussed other energy issues, including diversifying energy supplies to reduce EU dependence on Russian gas. 
(Agerpres, Hotnews, Mediafax, Ziare, Realitatea TV, AFP, AP - 18/05/09)
